gov.nasa.jpf

Class ListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpf.ListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JPFListener, PublisherExtension, SearchListener, VMListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BudgetChecker, CallMonitor, CGMonitor, CGRemover, ChoiceSelector, ChoiceTracker, ConstInsnPathTime, CoverageAnalyzer, DeadlockAnalyzer, DynamicAbstractionSerializer.Attributor, EventGeneratorFactory, ExceptionInjector, ExecTracker, InsnCounter, LockedStackDepth, MethodAnalyzer, MethodTracker, OOMEInjector, Perturbator, ReferenceLocator, SearchMonitor, SearchStats, SimpleDot, SimpleIdleFilter, StackDepthChecker, StackTracker, StateCountEstimator, StateExtensionListener, StateSpaceAnalyzer, StateSpaceDot, StateTracker, Statistics, StopWatchFuzzer, Trace, TraceStorer, VarRecorder, VarTracker

    public abstract class ListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements VMListener, SearchListener, PublisherExtension
    Adapter class that dummy implements both VMListener and SearchListener interfaces Used to ease implementation of listeners that only process a few notifications

        public void classLoaded(VM vm,
               ClassInfo loadedClass)
        Description copied from interface: VMListener
        new class was loaded. This is notified after the ClassInfo has been instantiated, but before the class object is initialized, i.e. clinit is called. The main use for this notification is to identify and store ClassInfos, MethodInfos, FieldInfos or Instructions that are used by listeners etc. in order to enable efficient identify based filters in the performance critical instruction notifications
